profile_positions.description:
Customs and Foreign Trade
Started as a trainee and went on as a full-time employee I was a member of Foreign Affairs Department and worked under the supervision of a legal director.
- Drafting texts of contracts with foreign contractors (suppliers and buyers) on English; 
- Preliminary review and amendment of contracts provided by counterparties on English; 
- Maintaining and systematization of the company's legal library; 
- Interaction with the customs clearance of the personal protective equipment's export deliveries;
- Analyzing of existing contracts and other documents for the legality of foreign economic agreements and the presence of entrepreneurial risks;
- Analyzing of the risks of signing a contract on the terms of the counterparty;
- Legal supporting in negotiating with a counterparty to conclude a foreign trade contract in Russian and English;
- Consulting in the field of foreign economic activity with explanations of the norms of Russian and international legislation;
- Analyzing of legislation with the provision of written opinions in order to make the right management decisions.
